{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Teachers described AI and art learning objectives for their students, developed lessons to use AI tools in creative learning, designed AI tools for supporting art learning in their classrooms, and reflected on the usage of AI in creative classrooms.",
    "We utilized the use-modify-create framework (Lee, et al., 2011), where teachers gained experience with AI skills, and used them to create their own AI tools and lessons.",
    "Teachers demonstrated higher confidence in teaching with, explaining and making with AI.",
    "For instance, teachers used the AI Art Explorer tool that helps creative learners reflect on the artwork and gain personalized feedback during art creation, and develop lesson plans around using AI Art Explorer in their own classrooms.",
    "Teacher-defined learning objectives ranged from using AI for personalized art feedback, investigating students' own art style (4 teachers), evolving own art style (4 teachers), expressing emotions through art (3 teachers), creative ideation (3 teachers), gaining knowledge in art history (3 teachers), identifying emotions in art (2 teachers), and art for social justice (2 teachers)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "We utilized the use-modify-create framework (Lee, et al., 2011), where teachers gained experience with AI skills, and used them to create their own AI tools and lessons."
  ]
}